Japanese Bought Net 334.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-03-03T00:00:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/japanese-bought-net-334-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Feb. 25 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in Tokyo.  Japanese investors bought 334.2 billion yen ($4.1 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 33.6 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 0.3 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 300.8 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 862.1 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 118.5 billion yen in stocks, and sold 30 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 713.6
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  